    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/22.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Sharp</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>442. Your 390, December 18. Request release Peralme as instructed. Emphasize fact
                    that he emigrated before reaching military age and has wife and children
                    destitute in this country. Say that apparently provisions of Article 17 of
                    French Nationality Law of 1889 should not apply to naturalized Americans who
                    emigrated before reaching military age, and that this Government cannot concede
                    the principle if the law is applied to such persons. Express earnest hope of
                    this Government that cases may be differentiated and Peralme and others in same
                    situation allowed to leave France.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
